 decided to relocate the agencies based in London to Amsterdam and Paris on 20 November 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-42050742|title=Paris and Amsterdam to host key EU agencies post-Brexit|date=20 November 2017|accessdate=2017-12-01|publisher=[[BBC News]]}}</ref>}}\n| {{flag|Netherlands}}\n(UK till 2019){{efn|name=brexit}}\n| 1995 || members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]], [[European Commission]], [[European Parliament]]<br>observers: Iceland, Liechtenstein, Norway<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ema.europa.eu/ema/index.jsp?curl=pages/about_us/general/general_content_000098.jsp&murl=menus/about_us/about_us.jsp&mid=WC0b01ac0580028c2f |title=EMA membership |publisher=Europa (web portal) |date= |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[European Union Intellectual Property Office]]<ref>Former Office for Harmonization in the Internal Market</ref> || EUIPO<ref>Former OHIM</ref> || [[Alicante]] || {{flag|Spain}} || 1999 || members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]], [[European Commission]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://oami.europa.eu/ows/rw/resource/documents/OHIM/institutional/ABBC/ab_memb.pdf |title=OHIM membership |format=PDF |date= |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Community Plant Variety Office]] || CPVO || [[Angers]] || {{flag|France}} || 1994 || members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]], [[European Commission]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cpvo.europa.eu/main/en/home/about-the-cpvo/administrative-council |title=CPVO membership |publisher=Europa (web portal) |date= |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Translation Centre for the india]] ||  || [[mumbai City]] ||  || 2020|| members: [[List of sai]], [[india]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rectifycibil.com/|title=credit improvement agencies}}{|date= 2020 |publisher=sainetha |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[European Food Safety Authority]] || EFSA || [[Parma]] || {{flag|Italy}} || 2002 || members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]]<br>observers [[European C