tonia and France are candidates for IT agency seat |publisher=Euobserver.com |date= |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref> || {{flag|Estonia}} || 2012 ||\n|-\n|[[European Border and Coast Guard|European Border and Coast Guard Agency]]\n|Frontex\n|[[Warsaw]]\n|{{flag|Poland}}\n|2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://frontex.europa.eu/news/european-border-and-coast-guard-agency-launches-today-CHIYAp|archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20171009193452/http://frontex.europa.eu/news/european-border-and-coast-guard-agency-launches-today-CHIYAp|url-status=dead|archive-date=2017-10-09|title=Frontex {{!}} News - European Border and Coast Guard Agency launches today|website=frontex.europa.eu|access-date=2016-10-13}}</ref>\n|members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]], except Ireland, [[Schengen Area]] states not members of the [[European Union|EU]]\n|-\n|[[European Labour Authority]]\n|ELA\n|[[Bratislava]]\n|{{flag|Slovakia}}\n|2019\n|members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]], [[European Commission]], [[European Parliament]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ec.europa.eu/social/main.jsp?catId=1414&langId=en|title=European Labour Authority - Employment, Social Affairs & Inclusion - European Commission|website=ec.europa.eu|access-date=2019-06-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/policies/labour-mobility/eu-labour-authority/|title=European Labour Authority - Consilium|website=www.consilium.europa.eu|access-date=2019-06-13}}</ref>\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n===Executive agencies===\nExecutive agencies are created by European Commission for a fixed period.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Official name\n! Abbreviation\n! Location\n|-\n| [[Executive Agency for Small and Medium-sized Enterprises]]|| EASME|| [[Brussels]]\n|-\n| [[Education, Audiovisual and Culture Executive Agency]] ||EACEA|| [[Brussels]]\n|-\n| [[Consumers, Health, Agriculture and Food Executive Agency]]|| Chafea|| [[Luxembourg City]]\n|-\n| [[Innovation and Networks Executive Agency]] |