itute for Security Studies]] || EUISS || [[Paris]] || {{flag|France}} || 2001 || \n|-\n| [[European Union Satellite Centre]] || SatCen || [[Torrej\u00f3n de Ardoz]] || {{flag|Spain}} || 2002 ||\n|-\n|[[European Police College|The European Union Agency for Law Enforcement Training]]\n| CEPOL ||[[Budapest]] (since 2014)\n[[Bramshill]] (2005\u20132014)\n| {{flag|Hungary}}\n(UK till 2014)\n| 2005 || members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]] without Denmark <br>associates: Iceland, Norway, Switzerland<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cepol.europa.eu/index.php?id=police-colleges |title=CEPOL membership |publisher=Europa (web portal) |date= |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Europol|European Union Agency for Law Enforcement Cooperation]]|| Europol || [[The Hague]] || {{flag|Netherlands}} ||1999 || members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]] \n|-\n| [[Eurojust|European body for the enhancement of judicial co-operation]] || Eurojust || [[The Hague]] || {{flag|Netherlands}} || 2002 || members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]] \n|-\n| [[Fundamental Rights Agency]] || FRA || [[Vienna]] || {{flag|Austria}} || 2007 || members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]], [[European Commission]], [[Council of Europe]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fra.europa.eu/fraWebsite/about_fra/who_we_are/management_board/management_board_en.htm |title=FRA membership |publisher=Europa (web portal) |date=15 April 2011 |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Body of European Regulators of Electronic Communications]] || BEREC || [[Riga]] || {{flag|Latvia}} || 2010 || members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]], [[European Commission]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.erg.eu.int/about/index_en.htm |title=About BEREC |publisher=Erg.eu.int |date=25 November 2009 |accessdate=23 April 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110226042929/http://www.erg.eu.int/about/index_en.htm |archive-date=26 February 2011 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> \n|-\n| [[European Systemic Risk 