arge-scale IT systems in the area of freedom, security and justice]</ref><ref name = agencies>{{cite web |url=https://ec.europa.eu/home-affairs/what-we-do/agencies_en |title=Agencies |url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120627121135/http://ec.europa.eu/home-affairs/policies/agencies/agencies_intro_en.htm |archivedate=27 June 2012 |df=dmy-all |website = Migration and Home Affairs|publisher = European Commission}}</ref> || eu-LISA<ref>{{cite web|url=http://europa.eu/about-eu/agencies/regulatory_agencies_bodies/policy_agencies/eu-lisa/index_en.htm|title=European Agency for the operational management of large-scale IT systems in the area of freedom, security and justice (eu-LISA) - European Union - European Commission|first=|last=Anonymous|date=16 June 2016|website=European Union}}</ref> || [[Tallinn]]<ref>{{cite web|author=Valentina Pop |url=http://euobserver.com/18/30994 |title=Estonia and France are candidates for IT agency seat |publisher=Euobserver.com |date= |accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref> || {{flag|Estonia}} || 2012 ||\n|-\n|[[European Border and Coast Guard|European Border and Coast Guard Agency]]\n|Frontex\n|[[Warsaw]]\n|{{flag|Poland}}\n|2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://frontex.europa.eu/news/european-border-and-coast-guard-agency-launches-today-CHIYAp|archive-url=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20171009193452/http://frontex.europa.eu/news/european-border-and-coast-guard-agency-launches-today-CHIYAp|url-status=dead|archive-date=2017-10-09|title=Frontex {{!}} News - European Border and Coast Guard Agency launches today|website=frontex.europa.eu|access-date=2016-10-13}}</ref>\n|members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]], except Ireland, [[Schengen Area]] states not members of the [[European Union|EU]]\n|-\n|[[European Labour Authority]]\n|ELA\n|[[Bratislava]]\n|{{flag|Slovakia}}\n|2019\n|members: [[List of EU member states|EU states]], [[European Commission]], [[European Parliament]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ec.europa.eu/social/mai