{"title_page": "Tanner Buchanan", "text_new": "{{Notability|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Tanner Buchanan\n| image        = Tanner Buchanan (28000180628) (cropped).jpg\n| caption      = Buchanan in 2018\n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1998|12|8|}}\n| birth_place  = [[Ottawa, Ohio]], U.S.\n| occupation   = Actor\n| years_active = 2009\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Tanner Buchanan''' (born December 8, 1998) is an American actor. He is best known for his roles as Leo Kirkman in the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] political drama ''[[Designated Survivor (TV series)|Designated Survivor]]'' and Robby Keene in the [[YouTube Premium]] series ''[[Cobra Kai]]''. He is also known for his role in the[[Nickelodeon]] television series as Mason Kendall\n\n==Career==\nBuchanan was born in [[Ottawa, Ohio]]. In 2010, he made his first appearance on television, playing a child role in the ''[[Modern Family]]'' series. Three years later he appeared in ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', ''[[Major Crimes (TV series)|Major Crimes]]'', and ''[[The Goldbergs (2013 TV series)|The Goldbergs]]''. He had recurring roles on ''[[Girl Meets World]]'', ''[[Game Shakers]]'', and ''[[The Fosters (American TV series)|The Fosters]]''. In 2016, he played his first main role on television, playing Leo Kirkman in the political drama series ''[[Designated Survivor (TV series)|Designated Survivor]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Burns |first=Geoff |date=March 4, 2017 |title=Lima native goes from Ohio to Hollywood |url=https://www.toledoblade.com/TV-Radio/2017/03/05/Lima-native-Tanner-Buchanan-goes-from-Ohio-to-Hollywood.html |work=[[The Blade (Toledo, Ohio)|The Blade]] |access-date=May 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Lesnick |first=Silas |date=September 29, 2016 |title=ABC Gives Full-Season Orders to Designated Survivor and Speechless |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/tv/news/771841-abc-designated-survivor-speechless |work=ComingSoon.net |access-date=May 6, 2019}}</ref> In 2018, he began playing Robby Keene in the [[YouTube Premium]] series ''[[Cobra Kai]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Fienberg |first=Daniel |date=April 25, 2018 |title='Cobra Kai': TV Review Tribeca 2018 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/cobra-kai-review-1105632 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=May 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Mendez |first=Michele |date=April 26, 2019 |title=EXCLUSIVE: \u2018Cobra Kai\u2019 Star Tanner Buchanan Talks Season 2, Training Process, and Being Part of the \u2018Karate Kid\u2019 Franchise |url=https://celebmix.com/exclusive-cobra-kai-tanner-buchanan-season-2-training-karate-kid-franchise/ |work=CelebMix |access-date=May 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Jake Squared]]''\n| Sammy\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Guests''\n| Bobby Bell\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Ellie''\n| Bowie\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[The Heyday of the Insensitive Bastards]]''\n| Bobby Bell\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Alone in the Dust''\n| Izzi\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Anything (film)|Anything]]''\n| Jack Sachman\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Max Winslow and the House of Secrets''\n| Connor Lawson\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Sinister Seduction''\n| Dylan Warren\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Painted Beauty''\n| Young Peter\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''Chance''\n| Colton\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Modern Family]]''\n| Kid #2\n| Episode: \"Halloween\"\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''Untitled Jeff and Jackie Filgo Project''\n| Jimmy\n| Unsold pilot\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''The Real St. Nick''\n| Cynical Kid\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''\n| Lucas\n| Episode: \"Idle Hands\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Major Crimes (TV series)|Major Crimes]]''\n| Michelle Brand\n| Episode: \"Boys Will Be Boys\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Ghost Ghirls]]''\n| Hero\n| Episode: \"Field of Screams\"\n|-\n| 2013\u20132014\n| ''[[The Goldbergs (2013 TV series)|The Goldbergs]]''\n| Evan Turner\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Growing Up Fisher]]''\n| Slade\n| Episode: \"Work with Me\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Mixology]]''\n| Young Dom\n| Episode: \"Fab & Jessica & Dominic\"\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Girl Meets World]]''\n| Charlie Gardner\n| Recurring role; 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\u20132019\n| ''[[Game Shakers]]''\n| Mason Kendall\n| Recurring role; 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[The Fosters (American TV series)|The Fosters]]''\n| Jack Downey\n| Recurring role; 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\u20132018\n| ''[[Designated Survivor (TV series)|Designated Survivor]]''\n| Leo Kirkman\n| Main role; 19 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Fuller House (TV series)|Fuller House]]''\n| Chad Brad Bradley\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[List of The Goldbergs episodes#Specials|The Goldbergs: 1990-Something]]''\n| Mike Stamm\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2018\u2013present\n| ''[[Cobra Kai]]''\n| Robby Keene\n| Main role; 20 episodes\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Deputy (TV series)|Deputy]]''\n| Brendan\n| Episode: \"10-8 Entitlements\"\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|4120909}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Buchanan, Tanner}}\n[[Category:1999 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Ohio]]\n[[Category:American male child actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:People from Ottawa, Ohio]]\n", "text_old": "{{Notability|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Tanner Buchanan\n| image        = Tanner Buchanan (28000180628) (cropped).jpg\n| caption      = Buchanan in 2018\n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1998|12|8|}}\n| birth_place  = [[Ottawa, Ohio]], U.S.\n| occupation   = Actor\n| years_active = 2009\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Tanner Buchanan''' (born December 8, 1998) is an American actor. He is best known for his roles as Leo Kirkman in the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] political drama ''[[Designated Survivor (TV series)|Designated Survivor]]'' and Robby Keene in the [[YouTube Premium]] series ''[[Cobra Kai]]''.\n\n==Career==\nBuchanan was born in [[Ottawa, Ohio]]. In 2010, he made his first appearance on television, playing a child role in the ''[[Modern Family]]'' series. Three years later he appeared in ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'', ''[[Major Crimes (TV series)|Major Crimes]]'', and ''[[The Goldbergs (2013 TV series)|The Goldbergs]]''. He had recurring roles on ''[[Girl Meets World]]'', ''[[Game Shakers]]'', and ''[[The Fosters (American TV series)|The Fosters]]''. In 2016, he played his first main role on television, playing Leo Kirkman in the political drama series ''[[Designated Survivor (TV series)|Designated Survivor]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Burns |first=Geoff |date=March 4, 2017 |title=Lima native goes from Ohio to Hollywood |url=https://www.toledoblade.com/TV-Radio/2017/03/05/Lima-native-Tanner-Buchanan-goes-from-Ohio-to-Hollywood.html |work=[[The Blade (Toledo, Ohio)|The Blade]] |access-date=May 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Lesnick |first=Silas |date=September 29, 2016 |title=ABC Gives Full-Season Orders to Designated Survivor and Speechless |url=https://www.comingsoon.net/tv/news/771841-abc-designated-survivor-speechless |work=ComingSoon.net |access-date=May 6, 2019}}</ref> In 2018, he began playing Robby Keene in the [[YouTube Premium]] series ''[[Cobra Kai]]''.<ref>{{cite news |last=Fienberg |first=Daniel |date=April 25, 2018 |title='Cobra Kai': TV Review Tribeca 2018 |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/cobra-kai-review-1105632 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |access-date=May 6, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Mendez |first=Michele |date=April 26, 2019 |title=EXCLUSIVE: \u2018Cobra Kai\u2019 Star Tanner Buchanan Talks Season 2, Training Process, and Being Part of the \u2018Karate Kid\u2019 Franchise |url=https://celebmix.com/exclusive-cobra-kai-tanner-buchanan-season-2-training-karate-kid-franchise/ |work=CelebMix |access-date=May 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Jake Squared]]''\n| Sammy\n|\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Guests''\n| Bobby Bell\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Ellie''\n| Bowie\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[The Heyday of the Insensitive Bastards]]''\n| Bobby Bell\n|\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''Alone in the Dust''\n| Izzi\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Anything (film)|Anything]]''\n| Jack Sachman\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Max Winslow and the House of Secrets''\n| Connor Lawson\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Sinister Seduction''\n| Dylan Warren\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''Painted Beauty''\n| Young Peter\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''Chance''\n| Colton\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Modern Family]]''\n| Kid #2\n| Episode: \"Halloween\"\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''Untitled Jeff and Jackie Filgo Project''\n| Jimmy\n| Unsold pilot\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''The Real St. Nick''\n| Cynical Kid\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]''\n| Lucas\n| Episode: \"Idle Hands\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Major Crimes (TV series)|Major Crimes]]''\n| Michelle Brand\n| Episode: \"Boys Will Be Boys\"\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Ghost Ghirls]]''\n| Hero\n| Episode: \"Field of Screams\"\n|-\n| 2013\u20132014\n| ''[[The Goldbergs (2013 TV series)|The Goldbergs]]''\n| Evan Turner\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Growing Up Fisher]]''\n| Slade\n| Episode: \"Work with Me\"\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Mixology]]''\n| Young Dom\n| Episode: \"Fab & Jessica & Dominic\"\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Girl Meets World]]''\n| Charlie Gardner\n| Recurring role; 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\u20132019\n| ''[[Game Shakers]]''\n| Mason Kendall\n| Recurring role; 6 episodes\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[The Fosters (American TV series)|The Fosters]]''\n| Jack Downey\n| Recu